  "prompt": "How do I know who is following me on Snapchat?",
  "response": "To see who is following you on Snapchat, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Snapchat**: Launch the Snapchat app on your smartphone.\n\n2. **Go to Your Profile**: Tap on your Bitmoji or the ghost icon at the top left corner of the screen to go to your profile.\n\n3. **Access Your Friends List**: On your profile, tap on the \"My Friends\" option. This will show you a list of all the people you are friends with on Snapchat.\n\n4. **Check for Followers**: If someone is following you but you are not following them back, they will appear in your \"My Friends\" list with a \"Subscribe\" or \"Add\" button next to their name. This indicates that they are following you but you are not following them.\n\nKeep in mind that Snapchat's interface may change over time, so if you can't find these options, make sure your app is updated to the latest version.",
